title: Grateful Dead Live at Grand Center on 1980-08-24
description:
Set 1

Jack Straw, They Love Each Other, Cassidy, Brown Eyed Women, Passenger, Peggy-O, Looks Like Rain, Althea, Let It Grow-> Deal

Set 2

Samson & Delilah, Ship of Fools, Feel Like A Stranger, China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider-> Drums-> Not Fade Away-> Black Peter-> Sugar Magnolia, E: Don't Ease Me In

reviews.review_text:
Hidden Gem This is one of those shows that slips threw the crack as far as heads commenting on it. I think it smokes from start to finish .  

Do you guys have the Kansas city show by chance if so cant wait till its uploaded

Great Recording! Best recording of this show I have ever heard. Jerry's vocals shine, and the dynamics are awesome. Way to go Mason, and thanks for sharing with all of us. I talked with some tapers there, perhaps one was you. See ya on the other side.
May Peace Be Yours, 
Grateful James

Went to show just for the heck of it. I was a 18 years old at the time of this show. I did not know much about the Dead at this period in my life. I did have the Touch of Grey Album. As the years past I and the help of Sirus channel 23 I became a fan of their Music,  I was so happy to find this show here and was able to downloaded it. The sound is amazing. Thanks to the Mason Taylor collection.
1980 08 24 Very nice show and an excellent recording! Mason Taylor you really knew your shit!
Overlooked Dont miss this spectacular China > Rider, and a very very nice recording too.
